What are the logistics of humans and anthro's having children? I've always assumed that it's the case that the mothers determine the species. Like a humie man and an anthro woman would have little anthro cubs, and visa versa. This solves a few issues, like preventing a bunch of disgusting mutt looking things from running around, makes it so that neither species is going to be bred out of existence while still allowing us to have children with our anthro women. And I also imagine that having a mixed family of a couple human looking kids and a couple anthro looking kids would be quite jarring and bad for the mental and social health of the kids, as well as even for the parents to an extent.

The children regardless of species would still inherit qualities and traits of the father such as hair color, eye color, size, skin tone to a certain extent, the usual deal with DNA distribution. In addition to that, no matter how well bred a lineage is the rule will still apply, with only very rare instances of a mother birthing a child of the opposite species look, and it will be even more rare for a half breed looking one to be born.

I've probably thought about this a bit too much but this seems a bit important.
